---

in the front end
npm i react-bootstrap bootstrap react-icons
it should be imported in the index.js
import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';
Navbar bg='dark' variant='dark' expand='md'
expand md shows the hamburger menu when the screen become too
small. and lg shows all the time

---

In order to use react router it have to be installid in the frontend
npm i react-router-dom
npm i react-router-bootstrap. help up to have link inside the nav bar. since we don't use <a href>

---

npm init in the proshop folder for the backend this will allow to create package.json file

add type module on the package.json so we can use the es module like import osv

npm i express in the proshop folder
npm i -D nodemon concurrently
-D for developement since we only use them in development
nodemon so we dont have to restart the server for every change
concurrently for starting the front end and backend togather

"scripts": {
"start": "node backend/server.js",
"server": "nodemon backend/server.js",
"client": "npm start --prefix frontend",
"dev": "concurrently \"npm run server\" \"npm run client\""
},
scripts on the package.json

npm i -D dotenv to hold the conviguration file
npm i axios in the frontend for the api

npm i mongoose
npm i bcrypt.js in the proshop folder
npm i colors

in the front end npm i @reduxjs/toolkit react-redux
